article.headline: Shockers make 10 free throws in final 3:07
article.story: WICHITA, Kan. (AP) -- Jamar Howard scored 21 points to lead Wichita State to a 77-62 victory over Creighton (No. 24 ESPN/USA) on Wednesday. The Shockers made 10-of-12 free throws in the final 3:07 to help decide the game. Until then, Wichita State had shot just 4-of-11 from the free-throw line. Wichita State (11-6, 4-3 Missouri Valley Conference) bolted to a 39-22 lead at halftime and Creighton (13-2, 5-2), which lost for the second time in its last three games, played a game of catchup throughout the second half. After Randy Burns scored a 3-pointer to give Wichita State a 65-53 lead with 3:48 left, the Bluejays could not cut the deficit to a single figure. While trying to get the upper hand, Creighton starters Johnny Mathies and Brody Deren fouled out. Mathies, who finished with eight points, left with 3:07 remaining and Wichita State ahead 67-55. Deren, who had five points, went to the bench with 2:33 remaining. Also in double-figure scoring for the Shockers were Burns with 15 points, including 10 in the second half, and Fridge Holman with 12. Nate Funk led Creighton with 17 points, and Mike Grimes added 14.
